==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[socle#French|socle]], from Italian [[zoccolo]] ‘wooden shoe’, from Latin [[socculus]], diminutive of [[soccus]] ‘sock’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈsəʊkəl/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A low [[plinth]] or [[pedestal]] used to display a statue or other art work.

